  <description type="morphology">Trees or sometimes shrubs, with few branches, usually at acute angles. Stem segments ± yellowish green, 10–30 cm; tubercles salient, elongate, (1.5–)2–3 cm. Spines 18–30+ per areole, yellow to light brown, aging dark gray, baggy sheathed; major abaxial spines deflexed to divergent. Flowers: inner tepals bright yellow. Fruits densely spiny; areoles 16–30. 2n = 22.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering spring-early summer (Mar-Jun).</description>
  <description type="habitat">Sonoran and Mojave deserts, edges of juniper woodlands, sandy flats, rocky slopes;</description>
